RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR MN-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAM SEZ dueled on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and edged clear in the lane, holding off a closer late. BURNING LEAVES raced off the pace on the inside early, saved ground around the bend, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground to the wire. EYES FLYING BYE chased the pace setter between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the three path and was outkicked in the lane. COLOR ME LEGENDARY dueled on the outside up the backstretch, came around the bend in the four path and faded in the stretch. BIG BOY MCCOY raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and showed no kick.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 5F Turf CR: 86. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 12 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Min nesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOEL'S ANGEL led the way on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, kicked clear entering the stretch and held that margin to the wire while drifting out mildly late. O'BABE trailed the field early, raced in the two path around the turn, began a bid passing the quarter pole and improved position late. BECAUSE pressed the pace between horses through the opening quarter, navigated the bend from the two path and kept on in the stretch. HEATIN UP raced off the pace up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and showed no kick. BID ONCE tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and faded in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 96. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, TRIAL OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At One Mile Or Over Since June 12 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLATOUT WINNER saved ground around the first turn, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the three path, launched a bid in upper stretch and got up for the win late. SURPRSINGLYPERFECT raced in the three path early, stalked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the far turn and dueled in the lane, getting caught in the final strides. LINE TO GAIN tracked the leader on the inside through the opening half mile, came around the far turn in the two path, dueled in the lane and gave way late. WORDS OF WISDOM saved ground around the first bend, led the way up the backstretch, gave way while racing on the rail around the far turn and continued to tire in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Line to Gain
ENTRY.OWNER: Fortunes on 4 Racing LLC Litfin Nevada Werner Dana Werner Mary Lou and Cordero D

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 4 5F Turf CR: 81. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, TRIAL OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-w inners Of A Race Since June 12 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAYZEE led the way on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, kicked clear in the lane and held that margin to the wire. MORGS WORLD raced off the pace up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the bend, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. ESSENTIAL BELLA stalked the pace setter on the inside through the opening quarter, navigated the turn from the two path and chased on to the finish. YANKEE AGATE raced in the middle of the pack up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path and improved position between horses in the lane. BIRDIE BE GONE tracked the frontrunner on the outside early, navigated the bend from the three path and flattened out in the stretch. HONEY BELLA chased the leader between horses through the opening stages, saved ground around the turn and weakened in the lane. CASINO QUEEN pressed the pace on the outside early, continued around the turn in the two path and faded in the lane. NAUGHTY NELLIE trailed the field through the opening quarter, raced in the two path around the bend and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 99. Claiming Purse 19500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 12 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 12 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $ 30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAY MAGICIAN raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and kicked clear in the final furlong. MACHO ROCCO raced in the middle of the pack early, swung out to the five path to began a bid approaching the quarter pole and improved position in the lane. FIRE SWORD led the field on the inside up the backstretch, continued to show the way from the two path coming around the bend and was caught in midstretch. WISE VERDICT trailed the field through the opening stages, saved ground around the bend and passed tiring horses in the lane. KIERKEGAARD raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, came around the turn in the three path and made no bid. LOVE MY JIMMY chased the leader on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the bend from the four path and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 6 7 1/2F Turf CR: 100. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 (MINNESOTA BRED $12,500) OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $12,500. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At One Mile Or Over Since June 12 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 (Claiming Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $20,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2fu rlongs and races for three-year-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THICK HAZE saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leader up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and kicked clear. SKIPPY'S STRIKE veered in and bumped with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, raced off the pace in the two path through the opening half mile, swung out to the four path coming around the far turn, began a bid entering the stretch and gained ground late. BIGFOOT CITY led the field from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the far bend and weakened in the final furlong. ARIES REIGNS saved ground around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second turn and finished evenly. MARK THE MOOSE raced in the two path early, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, navigated the far turn still in the two path and made no bid. BEAT THE HEAT trailed the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second bend and was outkicked in the lane. PAPA RIZZO was bumped and blocked at the start, raced in the three path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the far turn and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Bob Morehouse S. CANTERBURY PARK RACE 8 350 Y Dirt CR: 90. Stakes Purse 20000. FOR QUARTER HORSES, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH ARE REGISTERED MINNESOTA BRED. Free nomination by Wednesday, June 28. $200 to enter, $200 additional to start. Supplemental nominations of $800 will be accepted at time of entry which shall include all fees. Purse $22,800 of which 50% to the owner of the winner, 20% to second, 15% to third, 10% to fourth, and 5% to fifth. Weights: Three year olds - 125 lbs.; Older - 127 lbs. The Bob Morehouse Stakes will be limited to ten (10) starters. Preference will be given to horses with the highest total earnings in 2022-2023. Management reserves the right to cancel, change or postpone this race. Canterbury Park reserves the right to refuse any nomination or entry into this race. Failure to draw into the race wil l cancel all fees. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. The final purse will be reduced by the cost of any Out of Competition testing required by the Minnesota Racing Commission as a condition of competing in this race. Nominations closed Wedn
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DICKEY BOB duel, kick clear. RELENTLESS BABE duel, chase on. WESTERN RESERVE chase, late gain. EOS WHISKEY GIRL veer brk,outkicked. RELENTLESS LEGACY block/veer brk, trailed.
